TICKER_METADATA.name: Apple Inc
TICKER_METADATA.description: Apple Inc. (Apple) designs, manufactures and markets mobile communication and media devices, personal computers, and portable digital music players, and a variety of related software, services, peripherals, networking solutions, and third-party digital content and applications. The Company's products and services include iPhone, iPad, Mac, iPod, Apple TV, a portfolio of consumer and professional software applications, the iOS and OS X operating systems, iCloud, and a variety of accessory, service and support offerings. The Company also delivers digital content and applications through the iTunes Store, App StoreSM, iBookstoreSM, and Mac App Store. The Company distributes its products worldwide through its retail stores, online stores, and direct sales force, as well as through third-party cellular network carriers, wholesalers, retailers, and value-added resellers. In February 2012, the Company acquired app-search engine Chomp.

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Revenue per share

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Return on Assets ROA

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Asset Turnover
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Revenue over assets

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Book Value
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Book value of the share, assets - liabilities

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Book Value Per Share
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Book Value per each share

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Revenue
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Revenue

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Earnings Per Share Diluted
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: EPS for diluted shares

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Net Income
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Net income

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Profit Margin
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: This field is marked for DEPRECATION. Please use grossMargin instead. Profit Margin is calculated by the (Revenue - COGS)/Revenue

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Revenue QoQ Growth
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Revenue Quarter-over-Quarter Growth rate

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Debt to Equity Ratio
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Debt/Equity ratio

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Gross Margin
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: The margin of good sold, basically how much of the money the company keeps after selling their goods and services. (Rev.-Cost of Rev.)/Rev.

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Return on Equity ROE
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Return on Shareholder's equity; ROE=Net Income/Shareholder's Equity

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Current Ratio
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Ability for a company to pay off its short-term liabilities, Current Assets/Current Liabilities

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: FX Rate
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: The exchange rate used for the conversion of foreign currency to USD for non-US companies that do not report in USD.

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Shares Outstanding
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Outstanding shares

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Piotroski F-Score
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: 0-9 point scale to determine strength of company's financial position

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Long-term Debt to Equity
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Long term debt to equity

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Operating Margin
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Operating margin, or how much money a company makes on each dollar of revenue. In other words Operating Income/Revenue

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Earnings Per Share QoQ Growth
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Earnings Per Share Quarter-over-Quarter Growth rate

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Price to Earnings Ratio
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: P/E Ratio

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Weighted Average Shares Diluted
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Used to calculated diluted EPS. Considers all outstanding common stock plus all instruments that can be converted into shares (like stock options)

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Earnings Per Share
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Earnings per basic share (not diluted)

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Property, Plant & Equipment
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: A component of assets representing the total amount of marketable and non-marketable securties, loans receivable and other invested assets.

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: EBITDA
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: EBITDA is a non-GAAP accounting metric that is widely used when assessing the performance of companies, calculated by adding Depreciation/Amortization back to Earnings before interest and taxes

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Free Cash Flow
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Operating Cash Flow - Capex, How much cash is left over after reinvesting it in the business. Used as a measure to evaluate financial performance of a company

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Issuance or Repayment of Debt Securities
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Representing the net cash inflow (outflow) from issuance (repayment) of debt securities.

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Capital Expenditure
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Money uses to upgrade or acquire property or materials to maintain and increase size

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Research & Development
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: The aggregate costs incurred in a planned search or critical investigation aimed at discovery of new knowledge with the hope that such knowledge will be useful in developing a new product or service.

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Selling, General & Administrative
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: The aggregate total costs related to selling a firm's product and services, as well as all other general and administrative expenses. Direct selling expenses (for example, credit, warranty, and advertising) are expenses that can be directly linked to the sale of specific products. Indirect selling expenses are expenses that cannot be directly linked to the sale of specific products, for example telephone expenses, Internet, and postal charges. General and administrative expenses include salaries

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Current Investments
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: The current portion of Investments, reported if the company operates a classified balance sheet that segments current and non-current assets.

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Payment of Dividends & Other Cash Distributions
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Representing dividends and dividend equivalents paid on common stock and restricted stock units.

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Investment Acquisitions & Disposals
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: A component of cash flow from financing, representing the net cash inflow (outflow) associated with the acquisition & disposal of investments, including marketable securities and loan originations.

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Tax Liabilities
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: A component of liabilities representing outstanding tax liabilities.

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Net Cash Flow from Financing
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Net Cash flow from financing activities like issuing stock or debt minus dividends or acquiring debt

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Operating Income
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Operating income is a measure of financial performance before the deduction of interest expense, tax expenses and other Non-Operating items. It is calculated as gross profit minus operating expenses

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Net Income to Non-Controlling Interests
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: The portion of income which is attributable to non-controlling interest shareholders, subtracted from consolidated income in order to obtain net income

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Other Assets
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Assets that cannot be easily converted into cash and where the value of the item will be realized in a year

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Tax Assets
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: A component of assets representing tax assets and receivables.

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Issuance or Repayment of Equity
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Representing the net cash inflow (outflow) from issuance (repayment) of equity.

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Effect of Exchange Rate Changes on Cash
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Cash flow from exchange rate changes

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Net Cash Flow from Operations
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Cash flow generating from a company's operations

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Gross Profit
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Aggregate revenue [REVENUE] less cost of revenue [COR] directly attributable to the revenue generation activity.

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Current Debt
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Current debt - debt due within a year

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Accumulated Retained Earnings or Deficit
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: A component of Shareholder's Equity representing the cumulative amount of the entities undistributed earnings or deficit. May only be reported annually by certain companies, rather than quarterly.

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Other Liabilities
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Long-term liabilities (like debt) that are not due within a year

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Shared-based Compensation
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: A component of cash flow from operating activities, representing the total amount of noncash, equity-based employee remuneration. This may include the value of stock or unit options, amortization of restricted stock or units, and adjustment for officers' compensation. As noncash, this element is an add back when calculating net cash generated by operating activities using the indirect method.

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Business Acquisitions & Disposals
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: A component of cash flow from investing, representing the net cash inflow (outflow) associated with the acquisition & disposal of businesses, joint-ventures, affiliates, and other named investments.

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Current Liabilities
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Debt or liabilities that are due within a year

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Accounts Receivable
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Amount company will receive based on work already completed and delivered

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Cash and Equivalents
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Cash or assets that can be converted to cash immediately

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Accumulated Other Comprehensive Income
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Unrealized gains and losses - such as items that have changed in value but haven't been bought or sold yet

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Depreciation, Amortization & Accretion
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Depreciation, Amortization, and Accretion

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Current Assets
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Assets that can easily be converted to cash and can be used to fund day-to-day operations

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Weighted Average Shares
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Weighted average shares (undiluted)

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Investments
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: A component of assets representing the total amount of marketable and non-marketable securties, loans receivable and other invested assets.

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Preferred Dividends Income Statement Impact
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Impact of dividend on company's preferred shares

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Intangible Assets
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Goodwill and Intangible Assets

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Operating Expenses
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Operating expenses represents the total expenditure on SG&A, R&D and other operating expense items, it excludes cost of revenue.

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Inventory
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: A component of Total Assets representing the amount after valuation and reserves of inventory expected to be sold, or consumed within one year or operating cycle, if longer.

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Deposits
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Deposit liabilities, both domestic and international including deposits such as savings deposts

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Earnings before tax
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Revenue - Expenses and excluding tax

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Net Margin
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Net Profit Margin, or the Net Income as a proportion of Revenue. In other words, Net Income/Revenue

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Non-Current Investments
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: The non-current portion of investments, reported if the company operates a classified balance sheet that segments current and non-current assets.

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Total Assets
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Total assets

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Deferred Revenue
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Revenue that was received, but not yet paid out  including sales, license fees, and royalties, but excluding interest income.

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Tax Expense
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Tax expenses

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Total Debt
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Debt

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Cost of Revenue
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: The aggregate cost of goods produced and sold and services rendered during the reporting period.

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Accounts Payable
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Short-term debt the company must pay off within a year

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Net Cash Flow to Change in Cash & Cash Equivalents
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Net Cash flow - Total cash minux liabilities

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Net Income from Discontinued Operations
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Net income from discontinued operations

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Total Liabilities
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Total Liabilities

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Net Cash Flow from Investing
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Cash flow from investments made by the company

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Non-Current Debt
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Longer-term debt, typically greater than a year

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Earning Before Interest & Taxes EBIT
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Earning Before Interest & Taxes (EBIT)

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Net Income Common Stock
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Net Income applied to common share holders. Used in calculating EPS (earnings per share).

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Interest Expense
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Interest expense

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Consolidated Income
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: The portion of profit or loss for the period, net of income taxes, which is attributable to the consolidated entity.

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Shareholders Equity
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Shareholders Equity

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Market Capitalization
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Size of the company (shares outstanding * share price)

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Enterprise Value
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: An alternative to marketcap that's the theoretical takeover price of a company (marketcap + debt - cash and cash equivalents)

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Share Factor
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Share factor is a multiplicant in the calculation of [MARKETCAP]. For the overwhelming majority of companies its value will be 1. For American Depository Receipts (ADRs) and companies which have different earnings share for different share classes (eg Berkshire Hathaway - BRKB).

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: PEG Ratio
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: PEG ratio using the trailing 1 year EPS growth rate in the denominator

TICKER_DEFINITIONS.name: Price to Book Ratio
TICKER_DEFINITIONS.description: Price/Book value per share ratio
